        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XV_multi_scaler_Initialize</definition>
        <argsstring>(XV_multi_scaler *InstancePtr, UINTPTR BaseAddress)</argsstring>
        <name>XV_multi_scaler_Initialize</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_v__multi__scaler" kindref="compound">XV_multi_scaler</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>UINTPTR</type>
          <declname>BaseAddress</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initialize the Multi Scaler driver instance using base address. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function locates the device configuration based on the base address and calls the configuration initialization function. The instance must be initialized before using any other driver functions. The base address is typically obtained from the device tree.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the Multi Scaler instance to be initialized. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the physical base address of the device.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>XST_SUCCESS if initialization was successful, XST_DEVICE_NOT_FOUND if the configuration for the base address was not found.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This function is used in SDT (Software Development Toolkit) builds. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
